{
  "doc_id": "33785",
  "text": "Febrile neutropenia is generally defined as a rise in axillary temperature to above 38.5°C for more than one hour while having an absolute neutrophil count of less than 0.5 · 10 9 /l. Other definitions are also used like 38°C during one to four hours [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
